      "weather": "Fine",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TICKING OVER (1) goes very well here starting eight times for four wins and two minors. Was out of placings last time (16.33) at Launceston in a Grade 5, finishing fourth and beaten 5 lengths. Looks suited here and rates on top. ZARI EXACT (8) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 5.5 lengths at Launceston in a handy 16.02 beating Pinaroo Flyer. Draws out wide but goes well at this distance. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. In great recent form and expected to measure up again. POLLINATOR KEN (5) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 3 length win at this track in a handy 19.17. Awkwardly drawn but goes well at this distance. Has a strong record out of this box with three wins and a minor placing from seven starts. Will go close again if runs up to latest. MYALL CLYDE (4) can return to form after missing the top-three at this circuit last time out.",
